lines.text: Don't you want to get me one?
Well, I've never seen you take a drink before.
Honey, there are a lot of things you've never seen me do before. That's no sign I don't do 'em.
When I spend 8 bucks on a dame, I don't just go home with the morning paper, y'know what I mean?
It's not you marrying me. It's me marrying anybody. I'm sick. I am mentally sick, and I can't marry anybody, ever.
I didn't do it. I'd die before I'd hurt Bonnie.
Why do you suppose Ralph says those things if they aren't true?
